      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know there are helplines, but they just tell you to \"hold on\" or \"it gets better,\" and i just don't believe that anymore. nobody understands what it's like when the pain is your entire reality every single second. it feels less like a crisis and more like a logical choice. like, if a person is drowning, you don't tell them to just keep swimming forever, you realize they just need to be able to breathe. why is it so hard to see that just wanting the suffering to stop is a human thing to want?",
